In Salesforce Apex, you generate a PDF using a **Visualforce page rendered as PDF**.

---

# 1. Create Visualforce Page (PDF Template)

```xml id="vf1"
<apex:page renderAs="pdf" standardController="Account">

    <h1>Account Report</h1>

    <p><b>Name:</b> {!Account.Name}</p>
    <p><b>Phone:</b> {!Account.Phone}</p>
    <p><b>Industry:</b> {!Account.Industry}</p>

</apex:page>
```

---

# 2. Generate PDF from Apex

You can call the Visualforce page and get PDF as Blob.

```java id="apex1"
public class PdfGenerator {

    public static Blob generateAccountPdf(Id accountId) {

        PageReference pdfPage = Page.AccountPdfPage; 
        pdfPage.getParameters().put('id', accountId);

        Blob pdfBlob;

        if (!Test.isRunningTest()) {
            pdfBlob = pdfPage.getContentAsPDF();
        } else {
            pdfBlob = Blob.valueOf('Test PDF Content');
        }

        return pdfBlob;
    }
}
```

---

# 3. Save PDF as File (ContentVersion)

```java id="apex2"
public class PdfGenerator {

    public static void createAndSavePdf(Id accountId) {

        PageReference pdfPage = Page.AccountPdfPage;
        pdfPage.getParameters().put('id', accountId);

        Blob pdfBlob = pdfPage.getContentAsPDF();

        ContentVersion cv = new ContentVersion();
        cv.Title = 'Account_Report';
        cv.PathOnClient = 'Account.pdf';
        cv.VersionData = pdfBlob;
        cv.FirstPublishLocationId = accountId;

        insert cv;
    }
}
```

---

# 4. Trigger Example (Auto-generate PDF)

```java id="trg1"
trigger AccountTrigger on Account (after insert) {

    for (Account acc : Trigger.new) {
        PdfGenerator.createAndSavePdf(acc.Id);
    }
}
```

---

# Important Limits

* Cannot call `getContentAsPDF()` in bulk safely (callout-like limit)
* ✔ Use Queueable for large volumes
* ✔ Max PDF size ~1 MB (practical limit)
* ✔ Visualforce page must be optimized

---

# 5. Best Practice (Production)

Instead of trigger → use Queueable:

```java id="q1"
public class PdfQueueable implements Queueable {

    Id accountId;

    public PdfQueueable(Id accId) {
        this.accountId = accId;
    }

    public void execute(QueueableContext qc) {

        PageReference pdfPage = Page.AccountPdfPage;
        pdfPage.getParameters().put('id', accountId);

        Blob pdfBlob = pdfPage.getContentAsPDF();

        ContentVersion cv = new ContentVersion();
        cv.Title = 'Account_Report';
        cv.PathOnClient = 'Account.pdf';
        cv.VersionData = pdfBlob;
        cv.FirstPublishLocationId = accountId;

        insert cv;
    }
}



